  "id": "DoyleSpirals",
  "name": "Doyle Spirals",
  "shortDescription": "A beautiful arrangement of tangent circles mapped into 3D space.",
  "description": "Based on Jos Leys' work, this fractal uses the Newton-Raphson method to solve the Doyle spiral equations, creating a perfect packing of spheres that spiral infinitely. It includes an optional spherical inversion to create stunning closed forms.",
